# 🧠 Interactive Brain Activity Enhancement Using Hand-Based Exercises

An interactive, gamified rehabilitation platform designed to improve **motor coordination and cognitive function** using hand gesture recognition powered by **MediaPipe** and **deep learning models**.

## 🧩 Project Overview

This project introduces a game-based therapeutic environment to assist **Alzheimer's** and **cognitively impaired** individuals in enhancing neuroplasticity, coordination, and memory through structured hand gestures and exercises.

Developed as part of a research initiative at **Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham**, it merges modern **computer vision**, **machine learning**, and **real-time feedback** systems to deliver a cost-effective and scalable rehabilitation solution.

---

## 📂 Project Structure
├── pycache/ # Compiled Python files
├── model/ # Contains trained ML/DL models
├── utils/ # Utility functions and helpers
├── app.py # Main Streamlit app for game interface
├── game.py # Game logic and feedback integration
├── gg.py # Gesture recognition module
├── keypoint_classification.ipynb # Gesture classification (Notebook)
├── keypoint_classification_EN.ipynb # Extended/English version (Notebook)
├── point_history_classification.ipynb # Tracks gesture sequences over time
├── README.md # You're here!
├── .gitignore # Git ignore config
├── .gitattributes # GitHub linguist/language settings


---

## 🚀 Features

- ✋ **Real-time Hand Gesture Recognition** using [MediaPipe](https://google.github.io/mediapipe/)
- 🧠 **Custom CNN model** for classifying hand gestures (Open, Close, Peace, OK, etc.)
- 🎮 **Gamified UI** with real-time feedback, scoring, and leaderboard
- 🧾 **Progress Tracking** and graph visualization (Streamlit-based)
- 💸 **Low-Cost Hardware Friendly** (only requires webcam)
- ⚙️ Adaptive difficulty based on user performance
- 📊 Model accuracy: **91%+** in real-world tests

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Python 3.9+**
- **TensorFlow / Keras**
- **MediaPipe**
- **Streamlit**
- **OpenCV**
- **NumPy / Pandas**

