# NUNIX
NUNIX (Neural UNIX) is an experimental operating system project that can act as a second brain for the human mind. It is far from complete.
 
***

## About

See above and below for more info.

***

## Wiki

[Click/tap here to view this projects Wiki](https://github.com/seanpm2001/NUNIX/wiki/)

If the project has been forked, the Wiki was likely removed. Luckily, I include an embedded version. You can view it [here](/External/ProjectWiki/).

***

## History

This project was started early on as a concept for a UNIX-Like system in the human brain. Since this has never been done before, and the technology needed doesn't exist yet, this project is designed for the future. Precautions are currently being taken, so there will be several decades of preparation and stress testing to get the concept just right, as a lot can go wrong here. See [Council](#Council) and [Existential threats](#Existential-threats)

***

## Council

This project currently has a council in early Alpha. The council will be made up of neurologists, computer programmers, hardware engineers, and the top thinkers in the subjects of ethics and dystopian reality, so that all the possible dystopian endings can be closed.

[See the council by clicking/tapping here](/Council/)

### Pre-council decisions

Before I created the council, I had 1 critical restriction in mind, which I knew from day 1 would be the worst possible thing that could be done to the human brain:

Internet Access.

NUNIX will ***NEVER*** have Internet Access, as this would jeopardize the whole project, and make humans just devices that could be hacked and manipulated, which is a big and deadly scenario that will lead to Genocide and the end of humanity. Not even bluetooth will be supported.

***

## Existential threats

Some of the existential threats that can occur if this project is not done correctly include:

Mind control

100% authoritarian regime

Genocide of all races

The end of free thought

The end of human progress

and more...

***

## API

This project has a specialized API.

### HAP

HAP (**H**uman **A**pplicable **P**rogram) is the default package format for NUNIX, it does what the name says it is, its purpose is to be a human applicable, hyman applicable program.

### Programming

The HAP package has swappable programming language support via a magic keyword. The package format can be written in any programming language. Depending on its formatting, it will only be able to do certain things (such as HTML packages only giving off access to offline web pages)

