# fMRI Brain Activation Project

**Author:** Roshan Sathish Sandhya  
**Date:** December 2025  

## Overview
This repository is a personal side project exploring functional MRI (fMRI) brain activation patterns using the classic Haxby dataset (2001). The project visualizes category-selective neural responses in the ventral temporal cortex (e.g., faces vs. houses) with Nilearn and extends the findings to clinical relevance in Alzheimer's disease (AD) neuroimaging biomarkers.

The live website showcases visualizations, original research insights, recent advances (2024–2025), and a proposed future direction in radiology. An interactive Google Colab notebook allows users to run the analysis themselves.

**Live Site:** https://roshanss163.github.io/roshanss163radiology.github.io/

**Interactive Notebook:** [View Full Analysis Notebook](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1RTLQ0FJ0XbapK-8BNgY7_nXZn6qxqAMt?usp=sharing)

## Key Features
- **Visualizations:** High-quality glass brain plots, statistical maps, anatomical slices, and AD atrophy comparisons.
- **Research Depth:** 
  - Detailed methods and original synthesis linking Haxby ventral activation to AD hippocampal hyperactivity/hypoactivation.
  - Recent advances (AI multimodal fusion, preclinical biomarkers, etc.).
  - Unique future proposal: Adaptive AI-guided fMRI protocols for personalized diagnostic optimization.
- **Works Cited:** Comprehensive references from peer-reviewed sources.

## Technologies Used
- **Frontend:** Pure HTML5 + CSS3 (custom space-themed styling, no frameworks)
- **Hosting:** GitHub Pages
- **Analysis:** Python with Nilearn (interactive demo in Google Colab)
- **Fonts:** Orbitron & Exo 2 via Google Fonts

## Files
- `index.html` – Main website page
- `style.css` – Custom futuristic styling and animated starfield
- (Optional) `images/` folder – For locally hosted visuals (current version uses direct public URLs)

## How to Run Locally
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/roshanss163/roshanss163.github.io.git
