# Parkinson’s MRI Classifier with Self-Attention

This project implements a deep learning model to classify Parkinson’s Disease (PD) using 3D brain MRI scans. The model uses a 3D CNN encoder to extract local spatial features from the volumetric data, followed by self-attention (Multi-Head Attention, or MHA) to capture global patterns for improved classification performance.

---

## Dataset: Parkinson’s Progression Markers Initiative (PPMI)

This work uses MRI data from the [PPMI dataset](https://www.ppmi-info.org/), a large multi-center study designed to identify progression markers of Parkinson’s Disease.

> **Note:** Access to the PPMI dataset must be applied for, it cannot be given here.

---

## Model Outline

The model processes 3D MRI scans of shape `(96, 96, 96, 1)` using:

- A **3D CNN encoder** (Conv3D + BatchNorm + MaxPooling)
- A **Multi-Head Self-Attention (MHA)** block to model spatial dependencies
- Dense layers with dropout regularization
- Final sigmoid activation for binary classification

Custom features include:
- **F1 Score metric**
- **Binary Cross Entropy Loss**
- **Class balancing via class weights**
- Optional freezing/unfreezing of encoder layers during training

---

## Key Contributions and Use Cases

- **Classifies the presence of Parkinson’s Disease** from structural brain MRI alone, without relying on clinical symptoms.
- Learns **patterns of brain atrophy or regional structure changes** often associated with PD progression.
- Integrates **Multi-Head Self-Attention**, allowing the model to consider long-range spatial dependencies within 3D brain volumes.
- Provides a potential tool for **assisting radiologists** or acting as a **second-opinion system**, especially in cases where clinical diagnosis is uncertain.
- Offers a modular, clean architecture that can be adapted for other neurological imaging datasets or tasks.

---

## Metrics

| Metric     | Value    |
|------------|----------|
| Accuracy   | 0.741    |
| F1 Score   | 0.701    |
| ROC AUC    | 0.784    |
| Precision  | 0.728    |
| Recall     | 0.675    |


