---

## Methods

- Read GEO metadata and clinical annotations
- Combine expression and phenotype data
- Rank top 100 genes by differential expression
- Perform GO/KEGG enrichment using `gprofiler-official`

---

## Notes on WGS Matching
The GSE205450 dataset includes postmortem brain RNA-seq data. Complementary analyses were performed using peripheral blood RNA-seq data from the PPMI cohort, part of AMP-PD. While GSE205450 does not contain WGS data, such data may be available for overlapping subjects through AMP-PD.

> ref1: The authors state in this [article](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-023-39652-6) that:
> 
> ""Findings in the PD brain were corroborated by analysis of bulk RNA profiles in peripheral blood obtained from the PPMI, correlating with disease severity and clinical features of the disease.""

> ref2: [Early-stage idiopathic Parkinson’s disease](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10799891/)


